argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">On the eve of tomorrow=E2=80=99s House speaker =
vote, all eyes are on Texas
Rep. <strong>Chip Roy</strong>, an inveterate budget hawk and occasional ic=
onoclast, as the canary in the coalmine for any effort to depose <strong>Mi=
ke Johnson</strong>. With a razor-thin margin, and Kentucky Rep. <strong>Th=
omas Massie</strong> already saying he=E2=80=99s voting against him, Johnso=
n can afford to lose only <em>one</em> other House Republican if he wants t=
o hold on to the gavel. <br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">There are other potential nays, of course, but the
conventional wisdom on the Hill is that if Roy votes against Johnson, the d=
am probably breaks. It=E2=80=99s a pickle for Johnson because, while Roy is=
 about as conservative as it gets in the House=E2=80=94and Johnson, himself=
, was long viewed as a fellow ideologue=E2=80=94he is not a reliable vote f=
or leadership. And it doesn=E2=80=99t help that Johnson has pushed a number=
 of hard votes over the past year, occasionally leaning on Democrats (and p=
issing off the likes of <strong>Marjorie Taylor Greene</strong>, <strong>An=
dy
Biggs</strong>, <strong>Paul Gosar</strong>, Massie, and others) to keep th=
e government funded and send aid to Ukraine. Like a growing bloc of House R=
epublicans, Roy is a contrarian=E2=80=94but not purely one of the attention=
-seeking variety. When he takes a position, he=E2=80=99s usually uncompromi=
singly sincere about it, and that makes him potentially more difficult to t=
alk back into the fold. (While Democrats may loathe his views, privately th=
ey admire his consistency.)=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Of c=
ourse, <strong>Trump </strong>has been calling around to help shore up supp=
ort for Johnson, and has implied that he would back primary challenges agai=
nst members who don=E2=80=99t fall in line. But Trump has <em>already</em> =
<a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uktx=
clJLZ0dVS2NpblJSVzc5NkhobGJZY0U0az0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGV4YXN0cml=
idW5lLm9yZy8yMDI0LzEyLzE5L2RvbmFsZC10cnVtcC1jaGlwLXJveS1kZWJ0LWNlaWxpbmcvP3=
V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1UaGUrQmVzdCslMjYrVGhlK0JyaWdodGVzdCstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyO=
