argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Do you think his legacy will be that we=
 had a
non-functional president for the final year, and that Jill Biden was the on=
e running the show, like Nancy Reagan?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;mar=
gin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">In Bide=
n=E2=80=99s case, after year two, there was no <em>there there</em>, it see=
med. Anybody meeting Joe Biden knew that this was an issue. We really need =
to know who was in the inner circle in the White House, who was trying to p=
rotect him like that. You started seeing the Biden circle
trying to beat up on the press like CNN, MSNBC, <em>The New York Times</em>=
, <em>The Washington Post</em>=E2=80=94which, by and large, offered fairly =
positive coverage=E2=80=94and demonizing them, as if they=E2=80=99re the pr=
oblem. Biden had a career where he talked to the press=E2=80=94the press li=
ked him=E2=80=94and suddenly his aides started going after every reporter t=
hey=E2=80=99d see on TV saying Biden might be too old.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:=
0px;">As for what Biden
will be remembered for=E2=80=A6 I think the Inflation Reduction Act was <em=
>epic</em>, but because they buried climate in it, it didn=E2=80=99t satisf=
y climate activists. Climate change may be a key issue 100 years from now, =
where people are asking, <em>Who did what, when</em>? And we could say Bide=
n did more for climate change than anybody else, by the money he put into t=
hat Inflation Reduction Act, yet he gets no credit for it. <br/><br/>But th=
e central problem of Biden=E2=80=99s presidency, and why he didn=E2=80=99t =
get
reelected, is they only had one view of it. Which was, <em>You may not like=
 everything I do, but the alternative is Donald Trump</em>. That was their =
strategy. It=E2=80=99s smarter, in my view, to always be optimistic in Amer=
ica. Trump is an aberration from that; he marketeers division and fear. Bid=
en=E2=80=99s not going to beat Trump on that ground. Sometimes, Biden remin=
ded me of <strong>L.B.J.</strong>; he did great legislation, but there was =
no visual component, there was no <em>feel</em>.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
<strong>How much can Trump unwind of Biden=E2=80=99s legacy?=C2=A0</strong>=
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0=
;margin-bottom:0px;">Right after the inauguration, you=E2=80=99ll see Donal=
d Trump sign 100 executive orders. That doesn=E2=80=99t mean they=E2=80=99r=
e all going to stick. Some will get booted to the courts, and there will be=
 a lot that=E2=80=99s going to get through=E2=80=A6 I think Trump better tu=
ne out the
<strong>Bannon</strong>s of the world; get off a revenge tour; don=E2=80=99=
t target the press; sue organizations, like he did with ABC, but don=E2=80=
=99t target individuals. Trump=E2=80=99s going to have to watch that his ca=
binet nominees, if they get confirmed, aren=E2=80=99t exceeding their legal=
 mandate and losing public support.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0=
px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Could Biden=
 be seen more favorably if Trump=E2=80=99s second term is considered disast=
rous?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin:0;">I don=E2=80=99t wish for that in any way, shape, or form. =
We don=E2=80=99t want to see the president fail. But if Trump does fail, or=
 the country starts going into a recession, or worse things happen, there m=
ay be people saying, <em>God, we miss Biden</em>. That could happen. But on=
ly time will tell. Trump isn=E2=80=99t just trying to roll back Bidenism an=
d undo all that climate money and undo his executive orders; Trump would li=
ke to go all the way
back through <strong>Nixon</strong>. What brings <strong>Elon Musk</strong>=
, Trump, and many others together is money, and the federal government regu=
lating everything. They want to create a deregulatory federal government wh=
erever they can.</p></div>
